You have a hardboard in your bed instead of a bedspread?
I never will.
Maximum for one bed for visitors for one night.
However, if there are no ventilation holes, equip the board and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15 cm with spring bags (Taschenfederken) and a ventilation layer.
A polyurethane mattress should not be part of such a bed.
For single-position 14/18-slap mattresses, latex mattresses or sandwich mattresses (perhaps a combination of latex and coconut) are ideal, but it is always better for you to have a mattress with more slides, 28 and above, where the slides are folded in the lower part of the kidneys and so the rigidity can be regulated.
