To this day, I benefit from the contacts I made through the competitions.
The franchising of his hotel helped Lukas Pytloun to win the Best Individual Entrepreneur competition.
The winner of the Best Individual Entrepreneur contest for the past year was Lukas Pytloun, a 28-year-old entrepreneur.
His journey to success is like a movie.
Lukas Pytloun liked to travel.
And while abroad, he realized that there was a shortage of quality accommodation at a reasonable price in Liberec.
With his savings from his earnings while working abroad and with the help of a bank loan, he bought a small five-unit apartment building that was half demolished.
Knowing that he was still a third-year college student, it was a courageous move.
"The relationship between the quality and the price of accommodation in our area made me want to do something", says Lucas Pytloun.
He began renting the first apartment rebuilt to foreign workers.
He reinvested the profits in the building that he turned into a 54-bed boarding house.
Since then, his entrepreneurial activity has enabled him to open in Libérec 4 guesthouses, two style restaurants and two hotels with a total capacity of almost 300 beds of all categories of accommodation.
