The police released the 46-year-old contractor after 24 hours.
As to how he could influence a public tender, we can only speculate in view of the limited official information.
Pravo's spokeswoman Lubomira Cerna said that the police had actually made an arrest in Plzen at a separate workplace during the public competition.
"It was a customer and not an employee", she said.
The public tender, according to Cerna, is called "Call to propose rights for the transfer of land according to the Law on Land" and is set up when several candidates are eligible.
'These persons are offering, in the context of the appeal, a higher value of their rights of restitution which must be settled before the value of the land is announced.'
"According to the proposed rights, a ranking of acquirers is set up and the Land Fund then transfers the land to the person who proposed the highest rights", the Fund spokesman explained.
Lubos G. clearly had information on the persons who had signed up for the call and, being himself also a beneficiary, having purchased a large number of rights of return, he had proposed to the candidates in the field not to participate in the competition.
