In addition to the cases of children sitting down and drinking a bottle of alcohol after school, there are three seasonal waves that Pelikan says can be counted on: Witches' Day, New Year's Eve and the end of the school year.
"Either they drink in spite of bad results or they celebrate the start of the holidays".
