The US military has sent a new "smart" weapon to Afghanistan, known only by the code name XM-25.
The generals believe that this new automatic rifle will have an impact on the conflict there with the Taliban and "will change the game" in their favor.
The new weapon is like a super-precise cannon.
Its projectiles are laser-guided with a precision of a few meters.
The special 25 mm caliber ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly explosive explosive, actually works like small grenades.
We can program the munitions so that they explode not only in contact with the target but also at any point in their ballistic path.
So it can be used against an enemy who is hiding behind an obstacle, a wall or a ditch.
It's not protected from above either, and when a deadly rain of steel shards falls on it, it can knock it out of action as well.
According to Richard Audette, who was involved in the development of the XM-25, the new rifle is the first infantry weapon to use "intelligent" technology.
"The soldier uses it basically in such a way that he finds the target, sends a laser beam to it which determines the distance, thus obtains a precise point of aim, according to which he corrects his target site and presses the trigger.
"Let's say you aimed at 543 meters".
"When you pull the trigger, the gun charges and fires at a distance of 1, 2, 3 meters.
