But the commissioners ruled Wednesday night that the new religious center complied with local laws and would be aesthetically impressive.
"A lot of good people came to support him: Christians, Jews, Baha'is, you mentioned it", said Hadi Nael, president of the Islamic Center of Temecula Valley, speaking Thursday morning.
"I'm proud of that, as an American citizen".
