"If you go to bidding and there are few bidders, your prices will be higher".
"You have two choices: either you take the people in this market and say, 'We're going to negotiate a satisfactory deal at a good price.'
"But the idea is that it's not the price that's important, it's the skill of the people", Mr Laporte said.
This contract awarded to the Énergie gérance consortium is one of a long list of contracts of more than $50,000 won by the Parti Québécois.
The contracts were awarded by Hydro-Québec or SEBJ for the Eastmain-1-A-Sarcelle-Rupert project.
After verification, Le Devoir counted 109 engineering consultancy contracts awarded between 2002 and March 2010 to firms or their subsidiaries, in particular soil laboratories.
SNC-Lavalin won 22 contracts, Génivar won 16, Tecsult 14 and Dessau 10, not including its participation in Energie Gerance.
All the contracts have been negotiated.
