The lack of information and the doubtful nature of the information would calm the anxieties of 46% of consumers.
This is the second barrier identified by the Barometer, after the higher price of these products.
In addition, one third of Quebecers also express suspicion about the alleged performance of green products or services that are being put in their hands.
On the other hand, almost half of consumers in 2010 changed their habits and, in particular, changed the brand of one or more products to meet their beliefs.
61% also preferred to buy from local vendors and preferred to buy food products grown in their area, says the Barometer.
